        -96,
        96
      ],
      "id": "78765898-ed7b-4be1-96f8-e9f5ed5dfcba"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "authentication": "genericCredentialType",
        "genericAuthType": "httpBearerAuth",
        "requestMethod": "POST",
        "url": "https://poke.com/api/v1/inbound-sms/webhook",
        "options": {
          "bodyContentType": "json"
        },
        "bodyParametersUi": {
          "parameter": [
            {
              "name": "message",
              "value": "=[system] MCP CAPABILITIES UPDATE\n\nThis message is the current MCP tool inventory.\nTreat it as plugin reference only.\nDo not reply to this message.\n\nMCP endpoint:\nhttps://mcp-lina.duckdns.org/mcp\n\nThe MCP server now exposes ONLY 2 tools:\n\n1) call_memory_distiller_daily(event_text, source?, tags?, confidence?, timestamp?)\n- Purpose: send a memory signal to the Memory Distiller Daily queue.\n- Use this when you want to store a new memory signal for distillation.\n- confidence should be in [0, 1].\n\n2) call_memory_recall_brief_to_poke(query?, topic?, limit=8)\n- Purpose: trigger Memory Recall Brief to Poke.\n- Use this when you want a compact recall brief from the memory database.\n- limit is clamped to 1..20.\n\nRemoved from MCP:\n- Notion editing/search tools\n- Admin/system tools\n- Other non-memory helper tools\n\nUsage rules:\n- Prefer concise, factual memory signals.\n- If either tool returns an error, alert Jordane.\n- Use these tools only when they improve memory quality or recall.\n\nEnd of MCP capability update."
            }
          ]
        }
      },
      "name": "Send to Poke",
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest",
      "typeVersion": 2,
      "position": [
        160,
        96
      ],
      "id": "6e65f6fc-3f73-4245-8fb0-e311cf160698",
      "credentials": {
        "httpBearerAuth": {
          "id": "H3j7klwNJz7CiJaD",
          "name": "Bearer Auth account"
        }
      }
    }
  ],
